{"questionId":"9258","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>The following diagram shows triangle ABC, with <em>AB</em> = 6 and <em>AC</em> = 8.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><img src=\"__IMG__/7840b884a17d4284b6b6a3cfe107725e64d1d612.png\"></p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Find the area of triangle ABC.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\frac{1}{2} \\times 8 \\times 6 \\times \\frac{{\\sqrt {11} }}{6}\">\n  <mfrac>\n    <mn>1</mn>\n    <mn>2</mn>\n  </mfrac>\n  <mo>×</mo>\n  <mn>8</mn>\n  <mo>×</mo>\n  <mn>6</mn>\n  <mo>×</mo>\n  <mfrac>\n    <mrow>\n      <msqrt>\n        <mn>11</mn>\n      </msqrt>\n    </mrow>\n    <mn>6</mn>\n  </mfrac>\n</math></span>&nbsp; (or equivalent)&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>(A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p>area&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\" = 4\\sqrt {11} \">\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mn>4</mn>\n  <msqrt>\n    <mn>11</mn>\n  </msqrt>\n</math></span>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><em><strong>[2 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"9258","referenceCode":"SPM.1.SL.TZ0.1b","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-analysis-and-approaches","title":"Find the area of triangle ABC.","paper":"1","level":"SL","questionNumber":"b","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 3— Geometry and trigonometry","Topic 3— Geometry and trigonometry","SL 3.2—2d and 3d trig, sine rule, cosine rule, area","Topic 3— Geometry and trigonometry","SL 3.6—Pythagorean identity, double angles"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}